    <item>
      <title>Paul Brunzema</title>
      <link>//localhost:1313/author/paul-brunzema/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 31 Dec 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>//localhost:1313/author/paul-brunzema/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi there! Since March 2022, I am a PhD student at the 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.dsme.rwth-aachen.de/cms/~ibtrg/DSME/lidx/1/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Institute for Data Science in Mechanical Engineering&lt;/a&gt; at 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.rwth-aachen.de/go/id/a/?lidx=1&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;RWTH Aachen University&lt;/a&gt; under the supervision of 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.dsme.rwth-aachen.de/cms/DSME/Das-Institut/Team/~jlolt/Prof-Sebastian-Trimpe/?allou=1&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Sebastian Trimpe&lt;/a&gt;, and since September 2023 I am an associate doctoral researcher at the 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.unravel.rwth-aachen.de/go/id/ofgh/?lidx=1&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;UnRAVel Research Training Group&lt;/a&gt; funded by the 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.dfg.de/en/index.jsp&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;DFG&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Prior to that, I completed a bachelor&amp;rsquo;s degree in &lt;strong&gt;mechanical engineering&lt;/strong&gt; and a subsequent master&amp;rsquo;s degree in &lt;strong&gt;automation engineering&lt;/strong&gt; with a focus on machine learning and control, both at the 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.rwth-aachen.de/go/id/a/?lidx=1&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;RWTH Aachen University&lt;/a&gt;.
During my studies, I received the 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.rwth-aachen.de/cms/root/Wirtschaft/Fundraising/~elu/Bildungsfonds/?lidx=1&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Germany Scholarship&lt;/a&gt;, a 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.irt.rwth-aachen.de/global/show_document.asp?id=aaaaaaaaaavkdoz&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;MathWorks Fellowship&lt;/a&gt;, and was selected repeatedly for 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.rwth-aachen.de/cms/root/Studium/Lehre/Exzellente-Lehre/~dhky/Dean-s-List/?lidx=1&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;RWTH Aachen University&amp;rsquo;s Dean&amp;rsquo;s List&lt;/a&gt;. For my master thesis under supervision from 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://thisisalex.de/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Alexander von Rohr&lt;/a&gt; and 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.dsme.rwth-aachen.de/cms/DSME/Das-Institut/Team/~jlolt/Prof-Sebastian-Trimpe/?allou=1&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Sebastian Trimpe&lt;/a&gt; on parameter search in time-varying environments using Bayesian optimization I received the 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.sew-eurodrive-stiftung.de/en/#student-award&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;SEW-EURODRIVE Student Award&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My current research evolves around uncertainty quanitifaction when learning system dynamics and detecting changes in system dynamics with probabilistic quarantees. Furthermore, I am interested in Bayesian optimization&amp;ndash;specifically in high-dimensional and time-varying approaches.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
